    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what this 'indemnification' part means. it sounds kinda scary. can u explain it in simple terms?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in simple terms, is basically a promise where one party agrees to cover the costs or losses of another party if a specific bad thing happens. Think of it like this: if you mess up and someone sues you, the indemnification clause means you have to pay for their legal fees and any damages they incur. It's a way to shift the risk, making sure one party doesn't end up holding the bag for another's mistakes.",
      "source": "target",
